## Appendix B: Z-Transform Computation Examples

**Example B.1** (Z₁ Additive Identity)

- Z₁(37) = 30(2) - 37 = 23 [reflection across period 2]
- Z₁(127) = 30(5) - 127 = 23 [reflection across period 5]

**Example B.2** (Z₂ Multiplicative Collapse)

- Z₂(7) = 49 mod 30 = 19
- Z₂(11) = 121 mod 30 = 1
- Z₂(13) = 169 mod 30 = 19

**Example B.3** (Z₄ Reflective Inversion)

- Z₄(7) = 23 [complementary pair]
- Z₄(11) = 19 [complementary pair]
- Z₄(1) = 29 [complementary pair]

